{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Backend Architecture & API Contract Review",
  "description": "Reviews generated backend code against architecture rules (Node.js + Express, single-user, in-memory cache, minimal REST API, daily pipeline) and validates the GET /api/today response contract shape. Flags disallowed patterns (auth, sessions, DB, ORM, multi-user abstractions, overengineering) and any field drift in the API response.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "postToolUse",
    "toolTypes": [
      "write"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Review the backend code that was just written against these rules:\n\n## Architecture Rules\n\n**Required:**\n- Node.js + Express\n- Single-user demo backend\n- In-memory cache\n- Minimal REST API\n- Daily pipeline\n\n**Disallowed:**\n- authentication\n- login flows\n- session management\n- database setup\n- ORM usage\n- multi-user abstractions\n- unnecessary microservice patterns\n- overengineered folder structure\n\nIf any disallowed pattern appears, flag it and suggest the smallest possible fix that keeps the current architecture simple.\n\n## API Contract Validation\n\nCheck whether the backend preserves a stable API contract for GET /api/today. The response must normalize to this exact shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"generatedAt\": \"ISO_TIMESTAMP\",\n  \"stressLevel\": \"Low load\" | \"Steady load\" | \"High load\",\n  \"headline\": \"string\",\n  \"summary\": \"string\",\n  \"drivers\": [\"string\"],\n  \"recommendation\": {\n    \"title\": \"string\",\n    \"description\": \"string\",\n    \"timeWindow\": \"string\"\n  },\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"sleepHours\": number,\n    \"hrvDelta\": number,\n    \"restingHeartRateDelta\": number\n  },\n  \"calendar\": {\n    \"busyBlocks\": number,\n    \"nextFreeWindow\": \"string\"\n  },\n  \"sources\": {\n    \"oura\": \"live\" | \"mock\" | \"cached\",\n    \"calendar\": \"live\" | \"mock\" | \"cached\",\n    \"llm\": \"live\" | \"fallback\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFlag any:\n- Missing fields\n- Renamed fields\n- Field drift (wrong types or value shapes)\n- Unstable or inconsistent shapes\n\nRecommend the smallest change needed to restore the contract if any issues are found."
  }
}
